{"lemma":"مَرَدَّيْ","slug":"مَرَدَّيْ","root":"ر.د.د","root_slug":"ر-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَرَدّ","root":"ردد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38446","n38447","n15322","n15320"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bold"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rebellious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be accustomed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suckle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disgrace (someone)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rebellious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to polish, to level","tags":["causative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be beardless"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be callow or inexperienced"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fruit of the toothbrush tree"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Form-II causative of مَرَدَ (marada, “to be constant”).\n\nUnknown, possibly from a Middle Iranian cognate of Persian مورد (murd, “myrtle”). The “rebellion” senses of the root م ر د (m r d) may then be figurative after the tonic properties of the myrtle or the thermogenic, aphrodisiac and purgative effects of the toothbrush tree fruits."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38446","headword_ar":"مَرَدَى","root":"mrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraTaY","text_ar":"مَرَطَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38447","headword_ar":"مُرْدِىٌّ","root":"mrd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pole with which a ship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat, is pushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"propelled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mijo*aAfN","text_ar":"مِجْذَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n15322","headword_ar":"مُرْدِىٌّ","root":"rdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n15320","headword_ar":"مِرْدًى","root":"rdY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stone that is thrown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaApN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of rock with which date-stones are broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 417:) and accord. to ISk, ↓ the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of rock with which stones are broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one breaks"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stone which the strong man can hardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not at all, lift with his hands;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaA^apN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rdA^","text_ar":"ردا"},{"kind":"text","text":";)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which stones are broken; and with which they beat and soften a rugged place that they hollow out; and with which the hole of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lizard called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battered, when it is among large stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY qlEp","text_ar":"فى قلعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY qalaEapK","text_ar":"فِى قَلَعَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qlEp","text_ar":"قلعة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it softens and demolishes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, T:) the same word ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrdAp","text_ar":"مرداة"},{"kind":"text","text":") also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is guided to its hole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M:) [and accord. to Golius, on the authority of Meyd and the Mirkát el-Loghah, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper mill-stone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaApN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAdK","text_ar":"مَرَادٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) and this pl. is [also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAmK","text_ar":"مَرَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miromaApN","text_ar":"مِرْمَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrows thus called;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any missiles"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) Hence the prov., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda juHori kul~i Dab~K mirodaAtuhu","text_ar":"عِنْدَ جُحْرِ كُلِّ ضَبٍّ مِرْدَاتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Near by the hole of every dabb is its stone that is to be thrown at it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its stone by means of which it guides itself to that hole"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; applied to a thing that is near at hand, having no obstacle in the way to it; for the dabb will not be guided to its hole, when it goes forth from it and returns to it, except by means of a stone which it places as a mark to point out its hole: (T:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u","text_ar":"كُلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~K Einodahu mirodaAtuhu","text_ar":"ضَبٍّ عِنْدَهُ مِرْدَاتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Meyd) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every dabb has near by it its stone that is to be thrown at it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Meyd;) for the dabb has little knowledge, therefore it prepares not its hole save by a stone that may be a mark thereof, so that he who seeks it finds the stone that is to be thrown at the dabb near to it; therefore the prov. means that thou shouldst not feel secure from accidents, because calamities are prepared with every time, or period; and it is applied to him who exposes himself to destruction. (Meyd.) Hence also, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses assigned to it above, (S,) or in the second of those senses, (Ham p. 417,) said of a courageous man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamirodaY HuruwbK","text_ar":"لَمِرْدَى حُرُوبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the missile of wars"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mirodaY AlHuruwbi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِرْدَى الحُرُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the crushing stone of the wars"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaY AlxuSuwmi","text_ar":"مِرْدَى الخُصُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he whom they throw against the antagonists and who crushes them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ubi suprà:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo maraAdiY AlHuruwbi","text_ar":"هُمْ مَرَادِى الحُرُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAdK","text_ar":"مَرَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaApN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaY xuSuwmapK waHarobK","text_ar":"مِرْدَى خُصُومَةٍ وَحَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is very patient in the endurance of contention and war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse hard like the stone thus called;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in a verse of 'Antarah: or it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a horse that runs swiftly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~adayaAnu","text_ar":"الرَّدَيَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radaY","text_ar":"رَدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: or it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~adaY","text_ar":"الرَّدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"radiYa","text_ar":"رَدِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and syn. therewith], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it means, in that verse, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='N","text_ar":"رِدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an instrument of perdition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~adaY","text_ar":"الرَّدَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 207.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaApN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN mirodaApN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ مِرْدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) is used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel like the stone thus called in hardness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAdK","text_ar":"مَرَادٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodaApN","text_ar":"مِرْدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs of camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the elephant"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of elephants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the stones thus called; (M, TA;) or because of their heaviness, and vehemence of tread. (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirodFY","text_ar":"مِرْدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murodiY~N","text_ar":"مُرْدِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and with shedd [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pole with which a ship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat, is propelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being in the hand of the sailor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAdK","text_ar":"مَرَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAdiY~u","text_ar":"مَرَادِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) in the dial. of the vulgar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midorY","text_ar":"مِدْرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pronounced by them"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midoraY","text_ar":"مِدْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", without tenween, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midoraA","text_ar":"مِدْرَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midoraA^N","text_ar":"مِدْرَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; pl., with the art.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmadaAriY","text_ar":"المَدَارِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and vulgarly pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaAriY","text_ar":"مَدَارِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"also without the art.]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1073}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Meyd","TA","Lth","K"]}]}}